 <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#33333><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub140.ezboard.com/bgraffeswizardcompilation.showUserPublicProfile?gid=lunaltoadsnatcher>Lunal Toadsnatcher</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Sorcerer</span><br>  Posts: 589<br> <font color=#ffffff>(12/10/02 4:42 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Please note..</span><hr size=1> Hasten and his placeholders will despawn after about 20-30 minutes in my experience.  To speed it up just kill the placeholders, the most common of which are the drakes.  Oh and you do have a tracker with you, don't you?  He wanders the zone a bit once he appears so tell folk to let you know when they see him and tell them not to kill him - some of the folk there for giant loot get bored and start killing everything that moves. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub140.ezboard.com/bgraffeswizardcompilation.showUserPublicProfile?gid=frotznitfol>Frotz Nitfol</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Wizard</span><br>  Posts: 142<br> <font color=#ffffff>(12/10/02 6:41 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Please note..</span><hr size=1> Hasten loves to run down the path to the Feerott zone.  If you can station a bored guildie there or something to chase after him and hit &quot;H&quot;ail like there's no tomorrow one they find him, you'll be able to get your jboots. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#33333><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub140.ezboard.com/bgraffeswizardcompilation.showUserPublicProfile?gid=gvwiz>GVWiz</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Visitor</span><br>  Posts: 6<br> <font color=#ffffff>(1/3/03 10:19 am)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> .</span><hr size=1> If the Monk guy is up, just call it a day and come back another time. <br>
The best place to sit is at the crossroads near the Ferrot zone. Face towards the Western path. Hasten and all his placeholders will come right down that path and you can stop him with a hail.  <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub140.ezboard.com/bgraffeswizardcompilation.showUserPublicProfile?gid=alexiiacorin>AlexiiaCorin</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Visitor</span><br>  Posts: 1<br> <font color=#ffffff>(2/3/03 10:50 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Location</span><hr size=1> Two best places to catch Hasten;<br>
<br>
1) When you first zone into RM from Ferrott, at the crossroads. He runs from deeper in RM (the valley in front of you) and to the left of you<br>
<br>
2) Zone in from Ferrott and keep going straight past the crossroads. Make the next left. Theres a rock you have to jump/crawl over. Thats 'stuck rock'. He usually runs past there, sometimes gets stuck there. Bug or not, I dunno, but few really care...<br>
<br>
Took me 2 days to get him. But theres always some sort of tracker there farming HGs <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#33333><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub140.ezboard.com/bgraffeswizardcompilation.showUserPublicProfile?gid=izenblazeincindevesor>Izenblaze Incindevesor</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Sorcerer</span><br>  Posts: 682<br> <font color=#ffffff>(2/5/03 2:26 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Location</span><hr size=1> I got him last night ... the tracker I hired said he was wondering all around the HG hill area before he found him and spam hailed.<br>
<br>
<br>
Oh and I used 325 PP <p><!--EZCODE FONT START--><span style="color:red;"><!--EZCODE CENTER START--><div style="text-align:center"><!--EZCODE LINK START--><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=351590">Izenblaze Incindevesor</a><!--EZCODE LINK END-->  <br>
